quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
83,35,"seated upon their couches, they are looking around."
83,36,"Have the unbelievers been duly rewarded for their deeds? {1}",footnotes:1:There is a subtle satire in this sentence. In the world
84,1,"When the sky is rent asunder"
84,2,"and hearkens to the command {1} of its Lord, doing what it should;",footnotes:1:Literally: And listens its Lord’s command. However
84,3,"and when the earth is stretched out {1}",footnotes:1:When the earth is stretched out: when the oceans and rivers are filled up
84,4,"and casts out what is within it and is emptied, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
  84,5,"and hearkens to the command of its Lord, doing what it should.<sup foot_note="182643">1</sup>",footnotes:182643:Here, it has not been expressly told what will happen when such and such an event takes place, for the subsequent theme by itself explains this, as if to say: O man, you are moving towards your Lord and are about to meet Him; you will be given your conduct book; and rewarded or punished according to your deeds."
84,6,"O man, you are striving unto your Lord<sup foot_note="182644">1</sup> and you will meet Him.",footnotes:182644:That is, "You may if you so like think that all your efforts and endeavors in the world are confined to worldly life and motivated by worldly desires,"yet the truth is that you are moving", consciously or unconsciously, towards your Lord and you have ultimately to appear before Him in any case.
84,7,"Whoever is given the Record in his right hand"
84,8,"shall be called to an easy accounting, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
84,9,"and shall return to his people joyfully. {1}",footnotes:1:His kinsfolk: his family and relatives and companions who will have been pardoned even like himself.
84,10,"But he who is given the Record behind his back, {1}",footnotes:1:In( Surah Al-Haaqqah
84,11,"shall cry for “perdition,”"
84,12,"and will enter the Blazing Fire."
84,13,"He used to live joyfully among his people, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
84,14,"thinking he would never revert (to Us)."
84,15,"But no; (how would he not revert)? His Lord was ever watching him. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
84,16,"Nay; I swear by the twilight;"
84,17,"and by the night and what it enfolds,"
84,18,"and by the moon, when it reaches its fullness:"
84,19,"you shall proceed onwards from stage to stage. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
84,20,"So, what is the matter with them that they do not believe,"
84,21,"and when the Qur'an is recited to them, they do not prostrate {1} themselves?",footnotes:1:They do not fall prostrate: they do not bow down to God out of fear of Him. To perform a sajdah (prostration) here is confirmed by the practice of the Prophet (peace be upon him). lmam Malik
84,22,"Instead, the unbelievers reject it, calling it a lie."
84,23,"Allah knows best what they are accumulating (in their Record). {1}",footnotes:1:Another meaning can also be: Allah knows best what disbelief
84,24,"So give them the good news of a painful chastisement,"
84,25,"except for those who believe and do good deeds. Theirs shall be an unending reward."
